#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_instinct.md:1
msgid "Hercules DJControl Instinct (S)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_instinct.md:4
msgid ""
"This is the cheapest all-in-one controller with an integrated sound card. "
"The DJControl Instinct S is functionally identical to the DJ Control "
"Instinct, but has a brushed stainless finish."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_instinct.md:8
msgid ""
"[Manufacturer's product "
"page](https://support.hercules.com/en/product/djcontrolinstinct-en/)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_instinct.md:9
msgid ""
"[Forum thread](https://mixxx.discourse.group/t/hercules-dj-control-"
"instinct/12623)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_instinct.md:13
msgid "Setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_instinct.md:16
msgid ""
"The controller is a class compliant MIDI controller, so you should be able "
"to just plug it in and it should be recognized in Mixxx. No need for "
"drivers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_instinct.md:20
msgid ""
"Make sure to select the correct mapping for the controller and enable it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_instinct.md:22
msgid "Audio Channels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_instinct.md:25
msgid ""
"There are two outputs on the controller itself: the headphones output with "
"builtin volume control on the side facing you and the speakers output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/hercules_djcontrol_instinct.md:29
msgid ""
"In Mixxx the headphones output is on channels 3 and 4, so select the "
"“Channels 3-4” item to get stereo output. The speakers output is on channels"
" 1 and 2, so to get stereo output you want to select the “Channels 1-2” "
"item."
msgstr ""

